FORMER Kaizer Chiefs head coach Ernst Middendorp has joined Ethiopian Premier League giants Saint George Sports Club. Middendorp and Chiefs parted ways at the end of last season after losing the league title on the final day of the 2019/20 Absa Premiership season to Mamelodi Sundowns. The coach he has since found a new home in East Africa where he will be coaching for the first time. “Saint George appointed Ernst Middendorp as the first team head coach,” the club announced. “The former Kaizer Chiefs coach is expected to assume his post within a week. The Ethiopian Premier League is scheduled to commence the season on 3 December. “The experienced coach has almost two months to prepare his team for the new season.” Aside from his extensive stay in South Africa, he has also previously led Ghanaian sides Asante Kotoko and Hearts of Oak. Saint George have won a record 29 league titles in Ethiopia, to go with 12 national cups. They made the group stages of the CAF Champions League in 2017. They were leading the league with 23 points from 12 games when the 2019-20 season was annulled due to the COVID-19 pandemic.